args: Hot damn! Ya took that fiend down in one\nstrike! Those are some skills ya got, Zace.
C'mon, say somethin'. Yer startin' to weird\nme out over here.
Huh. Man'a few words, I guess.
Er, ya don't need to apologize for it.
Ranzal's just worried about you, Zace.\nHe's afraid you might be having a\nhard time fitting in.
I see. Sorry to trouble you.
Aw, I'm just bein' nosy. Not every day we\npick up an ally as dependable as you,\nafter all.
Back in my merc days, I had my share\nof tangles with the Azm Tribe.\nI know their strength real well.
A group of hunters that live waaay far from\nhere. They're known for makin' tools and\nwhatnot out'a animal bones.
And is that why Zace wears armor made\nfrom bones?
Hey, if the guy keeps fightin' like this,\nhe can wear an outfit made of tin cans\nfar as I'm concerned.
And on that note, let's get goin', Zace.\nWe'll celebrate our victory with some grub!
Heh. Sounds like somebody's happy\nto be here.
Feast yer eyes on that gigantic skull, boys!\nThem fangs're right scary, ain't they?!
C'mon! Ya really gonna give us attitude\nafter we went to the trouble of takin' down\na huge beastie like that?
This varmint mighta attacked the village!\nYou oughta be thankin' us for our service!
O-oh, I'm quite grateful! Really I am!\nI just don't especially want bones shoved\nin my face like this...
Like you'da believed us if we didn't show\nya! Now go on—give it a real good look!
What a bunch of creeps. I'm gonna go—
It is shocking how you people have such\nbrazen, unearned confidence despite your\nevery word being utter nonsense.
Who the hell are you, bone boy?!
That skull comes from a species of\nhippopotamus called odotamus.
Its body may be quite large, but it's a\ndocile creature that feeds only on grass.\nIt's nowhere near the brute you described.
Ya got any proof of that, pal?!
That skull's front teeth are fang-shaped,\nbut the molars have the flat, millstone-like\nstructure characteristic of the odotamus.
You guys wanted everyone around town to\ntreat ya like a couple of big dogs, yeah?\nGuess it didn't work out for ya.
Maybe you oughta scram before ya\nembarrass yerselves any more.
You sure know your animal bones, Zace.\nIs everyone from the Azm Tribe like that?
Sounds about right for a buncha folks\nwhat make weapons and armor and\neveryday goods outta bones.
...That's not exactly the whole story.\nI am simply a fan of bones.
My hobby of collecting bones is unusual\neven among the people of my tribe.
In fact, I joined you all because I believed\nit would be a good chance to collect rare\nfiend bones.
I'm sorry for not mentioning it. I was\nworried it might seem distasteful,\nand so kept the matter to myself.
What're you on about, Zace?!\nAin't nobody got a problem with it!
He's right. You don't have to keep the\nthings you like a secret.
Truly. In fact, here's my secret: I love\nstuffin' my face with food! Pretty sure it\nblows Cleo's mind on a daily basis.
Ha ha! You might be right about that.\nSo as you can see, Zace, there's no need\nto hide your passions with us.
Wait, is that a smile? I didn't know ya\nCOULD smile! Well, ain't that a first?
Heh! I guess you're getting used to being\nwith us, huh?
I suppose you may be right.
